						               													<description>After being thrown into the new lands of Thessyria, the armies of the Accordlands find the land ruled by a mysterious otherworldly race, The Chosen. All resistance in the once proud desert empire has been squashed by the new tyrants. All resistance? Scouts return with reports, that not everything might be as the new rulers wish. Nothrog raiders emerge from the mangrove swamps of Eban-Tarsis and in the port city of Takkaz drunken sailors tell wild stories of ghost ships drifting in the winds and strange lights under the surface. Could the rumors be true of an Elven Empire leagues under the sea?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The second expansion arc for the increasingly successful 4th Edition of the &amp;quot;game you already know how to play&amp;quot; centers around the skirmishes along the long seashore of Thessyria. It explores the Water aspect of the new elemental magic system and features the first heroes that players could win for their faction in the world-wide Winter Campaign event series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Justice of the Black SunTwo Decks with 110 Cards and Rulebook enclosed - everything you need to start playing with a friend.&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Ships laden with horses and armored knights have arrived in Akkaz. Led by their iron-fisted Commander Kaiten the Order of the Black Sun intends to set up a new chapter and to recover from their recent losses. Watching them from the mangrove swamps of southern Eban-Tarsis Grilt Fenstalker only waits for them to bring their treasures to him. Will the might of Deverenia prevail in such unfamiliar terrain?&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
